EDF Wind Farm

 Sunday, April 7, 2019
Birds Landing, California—

When I visited Mt Diablo, I saw an expansive wind farm on the summit. It is located in Birds Landing, south of Sacramento.

Birds Landing, California

Mount Diablo

 Saturday, March 16, 2019
Mount Diablo State Park, California—

Mt Diablo is one of the highest points in San Francisco Bay Area. On a clear day, you can even see Sierra Nevada! I drove to the summit. The view along the way is breathtaking!

Mount Diablo State Park, California

Carmel by the Sea

 Saturday, March 9, 2019
Carmel by the Sea, California—

I went to the highly anticipated coastal town Carmel by the Sea, and drove the 17-mile scenic drive. It is well while it!

The Spanish Bay

The Lone Cypress

On my way back, I visited Walton Lighthouse in Santa Cruz.

Again, I saw rainbow during my weekend trip!

Carmel by the Sea, California

Pigeon Point Lighthouse

 Saturday, February 23, 2019
Pigeon Point Lighthouse, California—

On a Feburary weekend, I visited Pigeon Point Lighthouse south of Bay area. It is an ideal place to propose. Note: it is better to visit in the morning near sunrise.

Wildflowers encountered on my way to the lighthouse, 37°24'41.1"N 122°25'22.2"W

Also tried long exposure for the first time!

Pigeon Point Lighthouse, California

Point Reyes

 Sunday, February 3, 2019
Point Reyes, California—

On a Feburary weekend, I visited Point Reyes north of San Francisco.

Chimney Rock Trail

Cypress Tree Tunnel

It was raining lightly that day. I saw five or six rainbows on my way back. It was rainbow Sunday!

Point Reyes, California
